#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:1
msgid "DB Type Layer"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:3
msgid ""
"The LDE backend uses a three-layer type pattern to safely bridge PostgreSQL "
"row data and service-layer domain objects. This pattern was introduced in "
"v1.3.0 for the asset storage service and extended to the RoPA service in "
"v1.4.0. It eliminates implicit `any` casts that TypeScript strict mode "
"rejects on some platforms and keeps the mapping logic in one testable place."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:7
msgid "The three layers"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:8
msgid ""
"PostgreSQL\n"
"    │\n"
"    │  pg driver returns raw rows\n"
"    ▼\n"
"src/db/types.ts          — DB row types       (snake_case, pg-native types)\n"
"    │\n"
"    │  mappers transform row → domain object\n"
"    ▼\n"
"src/db/mappers.ts        — mapper functions   (one per entity)\n"
"    │\n"
"    │  services work exclusively with domain types\n"
"    ▼\n"
"src/domain/types.ts      — domain types       (camelCase, serialisable)\n"
"src/types/ropa.types.ts  — RoPA domain types  (camelCase, serialisable)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:27
msgid "DB row types (`src/db/types.ts`)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:29
msgid ""
"Each type mirrors the exact column names and pg-native TypeScript types for "
"one database table. The `pg` driver maps PostgreSQL types as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "PostgreSQL type"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "TypeScript type"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "`TEXT`, `VARCHAR`, `UUID`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "`string`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "`TEXT` (nullable)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "`string | null`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "`BOOLEAN`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "`boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "`INTEGER`, `SERIAL`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "`number`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "`TIMESTAMPTZ`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "`Date`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "`JSONB`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid ""
"`string` (returned as parsed object by pg, but typed as string for safety — "
"mappers handle both)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "`TEXT[]`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:31
msgid "`string[] | null`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:41
msgid ""
"// Example — process_definitions table\n"
"export type BpmnRow = {\n"
"  lde_id: string;\n"
"  bpmn_process_id: string;\n"
"  name: string;\n"
"  description: string | null;\n"
"  xml: string;\n"
"  process_role: string;\n"
"  called_element: string | null;\n"
"  linked_dmn_templates: string[] | null;\n"
"  status: string;\n"
"  readonly: boolean;\n"
"  schema_version: number;\n"
"  created_at: Date;\n"
"  updated_at: Date;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:60
msgid "These types are passed as the generic parameter to `pool.query<T>()`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:61
msgid ""
"const { rows } = await pool.query<BpmnRow>(\n"
"  `SELECT lde_id, bpmn_process_id, ... FROM process_definitions`\n"
");"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:67
msgid ""
"TypeScript now knows the exact shape of each row. No `as` casts, no "
"`unknown` index access."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:71
msgid "Domain types (`src/domain/types.ts`, `src/types/ropa.types.ts`)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:73
msgid ""
"Domain types use camelCase property names and serialisable types. `Date` "
"objects from `pg` are converted to ISO strings so service return values can "
"be sent directly to `res.json()` without a secondary serialisation step."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:74
msgid ""
"// Example — domain type for process_definitions\n"
"export type Bpmn = {\n"
"  id: string;\n"
"  bpmnProcessId: string;\n"
"  name: string;\n"
"  description?: string;\n"
"  xml: string;\n"
"  processRole: string;\n"
"  calledElement?: string;\n"
"  linkedDmnTemplates: string[];\n"
"  status: string;\n"
"  readonly: boolean;\n"
"  schemaVersion: number;\n"
"  createdAt: Date;   // kept as Date — res.json() calls .toISOString() "
"automatically\n"
"  updatedAt: Date;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:93
msgid ""
"RoPA types live in `src/types/ropa.types.ts` rather than `src/domain/"
"types.ts` because they are shared with the frontend (via the frontend mirror "
"at `packages/frontend/src/types/ropa.types.ts`). The RoPA domain types use "
"`string` for `createdAt` / `updatedAt` because the mappers call `.toISOString"
"()` explicitly before returning."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:97
msgid "Mappers (`src/db/mappers.ts`)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:99
msgid ""
"Each mapper is a pure function that takes a typed row and returns a typed "
"domain object. This is the only place where snake_case → camelCase "
"conversion happens, `null` → `undefined` coercion happens, `Date` → `string` "
"(`.toISOString()`) conversion happens where needed, and JSON string → object "
"parsing happens defensively for JSONB columns."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:100
msgid ""
"export function mapBpmn(row: BpmnRow): Bpmn {\n"
"  return {\n"
"    id:                  row.lde_id,\n"
"    bpmnProcessId:       row.bpmn_process_id,\n"
"    name:                row.name,\n"
"    description:         row.description ?? undefined,\n"
"    xml:                 row.xml,\n"
"    processRole:         row.process_role,\n"
"    calledElement:       row.called_element ?? undefined,\n"
"    linkedDmnTemplates:  row.linked_dmn_templates ?? [],\n"
"    status:              row.status,\n"
"    readonly:            row.readonly,\n"
"    schemaVersion:       row.schema_version,\n"
"    createdAt:           row.created_at,\n"
"    updatedAt:           row.updated_at,\n"
"  };\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:120
msgid "The JSONB defensive guard used in `mapForm` and `mapDocument`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:121
msgid "schema: typeof r.schema === 'string' ? JSON.parse(r.schema) : r.schema,"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:125
msgid ""
"The `pg` driver returns JSONB columns as already-parsed objects, so the "
"`JSON.parse` branch will never fire in normal operation. The guard exists "
"for resilience if a test fixture or a future driver version returns a raw "
"string."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:129
msgid "Services"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:131
msgid ""
"Services import the row types, domain types, and mappers. They never use "
"`as` casts on query results:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cdb-type-layer.md:132
msgid ""
"import { BpmnRow } from '../db/types';\n"
"import { Bpmn }    from '../domain/types';\n"
"import { mapBpmn } from '../db/mappers';\n"
"\n"
"export async function listBpmn(): Promise<Bpmn[]> {\n"
"  if (!pool) return [];\n"
"  const { rows } = await pool.query<BpmnRow>(\n"
"    `SELECT ... FROM process_definitions ORDER BY updated_at DESC`\n"
"  );\n"
"  return rows.map(mapBpmn);\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

